{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17592494","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17592494"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:15:37+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:15:37+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15254"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15254","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15254"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7945"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65972"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7945","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7945"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15254"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51421"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19344"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19347"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65972","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65972"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA pathologist is examining a biopsy specimen from an oesophageal mass (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following histological features is most characteristic of a squamous cell carcinoma?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Paneth cells","Granulomas","Signet ring cells","Keratin pearls","Parietal cells"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPaneth cells\u003C/strong\u003E are normally found in the small intestine crypts and contain eosinophilic secretory granules. \u003Cstrong\u003EGranulomas\u003C/strong\u003E are organised collections of epithelioid macrophages seen in conditions like tuberculosis. \u003Cstrong\u003ESignet ring cells\u003C/strong\u003E are characteristic of certain adenocarcinomas, particularly of gastric origin.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKeratin pearls\u003C/strong\u003E are a key diagnostic feature of well-differentiated squamous cell carcinoma, representing abnormal keratinisation in concentric whorls of squamous cells. \u003Cstrong\u003EParietal cells\u003C/strong\u003E are normally found in gastric glands and produce hydrochloric acid.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther histological features of oesophageal squamous cell carcinoma include intercellular bridges, nuclear pleomorphism, and abnormal mitoses.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Squamous cell carcinoma of the oesophagus shows keratin pearls, intercellular bridges, and varying degrees of differentiation on histology.","Keratin pearls are concentrically layered arrangements of squamous cells showing central keratinisation, characteristic of well-differentiated squamous cell carcinoma."],"references":["Wang GQ, Abnet CC, Shen Q, Lewin KJ, Sun XD, Roth MJ, Qiao YL, Mark SD, Dong ZW, Taylor PR, Dawsey SM. Histological precursors of oesophageal squamous cell carcinoma: results from a 13 year prospective follow up study in a high risk population. Gut. 2005 Feb;54(2):187-92. doi: 10.1136/gut.2004.046631. PMID: 15647178; PMCID: PMC1774842.","Codipilly DC, Wang KK. Squamous Cell Carcinoma of the Esophagus. Gastroenterol Clin North Am. 2022 Sep;51(3):457-484. doi: 10.1016/j.gtc.2022.06.005. Epub 2022 Aug 29. PMID: 36153105.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (20